  ). It is now also widely used as a short form of   Nancy ."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705210,"age":10,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705212,"age":30,"year":"1620","julianDay":2312753,"title":"The Pilgrims Board the Mayflower","description":"\"The Pilgrims boarded the Mayflower in search of religious freedom in the New World in September 1620. The Mayflower set sail from Plymouth, England, with 102 passengers, 40 of whom called themselves \"\"Saints.\"\" After two stormy months at sea, the ship reached the New World. Nearly half of the group died during their first winter due to malnutrition and the harsh New England winter.\"","url":"https://www.themayflowersociety.org/the-pilgrims/pilgrim-history","urlTitle":"The Mayflower Society - Pilgrim History","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Anne Gifford was born on 7 May 1589, in Lambourn, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom as the daughter of John Gifford and Anne Gifford. She had at least 1 son and 1 daughter with James Hartshorne. She died about 1640, in Berkshire, England, at the age of 52."},"et":{"7 May 1589–about 1640":"7. mai 1589–umbes 1640","1589–1640":"1589–1640","1634–Female":"1634–Surnud","1585–1631":"1585–1631","1614–1683":"1614–1683","1615–Female":"1615–Surnud","1569–Male":"1569–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","7 May 1589":"7. mai 1589","18 May 1614":"18. mai 1614","1569":"1569","1634":"1634","1600":"1600","1589":"1589","1631":"1631","1620":"1620","1585":"1585","1640":"1640","1683":"